          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "69-TM-169",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 1.0
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " High purity natural Tm",
                " Physical type:        Metal",
                " Chemical composition: Element (Thulium)",
                " Samples were prepared by evaporation onto 0.002 mm Al",
                "  backing.",
                " Thickness of the Tm layer varied between 106 and 356",
                "  ug/cm2. Thickness was determined by proton micro",
                "  beam using PIXE method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LEGE",
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA",
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The energy of the alpha beam was between E = 11.5 MeV",
                " and 17.5 MeV, covered with 0.5 MeV-1 MeV steps with",
                " beam currents of typically 2 uA.",
                "After the beam-defining aperture, the chamber was",
                " insulated and secondary electron suppression voltage",
                " of 300 V was applied at the entrance of the chamber.",
                "The collected charge in each irradiation was between",
                " 50 mC and 250 mC.",
                "S factors were derived from the averaged results of",
                " the irradiations weighted by the statistical",
                " uncertainty of the measured values.",
                "The effective center of mass energies (Ec.m.) take",
                " into account the energy loss of the beam in the",
                "  target."
              ]
            }
          ],
